{{Infobox company | name = Hotchkiss Ordnance Company | logo = | caption = | type = | foundation = [[Paris, France]] ({{Start date|1875}}) | founder = [[Benjamin B. Hotchkiss]] | defunct = | location_city = [[Paris, France|Paris]] | location_country = [[France]] | industry = [[Manufacturing]] | products = {{ubl|Armaments|Munitions}} }} [[File:Hotchkiss & Co advertisement clipping for Revolving Cannon 11-28-1885.jpg|thumb|An advertisement by Hotchkiss & Co. for revolving cannon, published in November 1885]] [[File:Hotchkiss Ordnance Co advertisement clipping for Howell torpedoes 11-24-1888.jpg|thumb|A Hotchkiss Ordnance Company advertisement for [[Howell torpedo]]es, published November 1888]] The '''Hotchkiss Ordnance Company''' was an [[English people|English]] [[armaments]] manufacturer founded by [[American people|American]] ordnance [[engineer]] [[Benjamin B. Hotchkiss]].
==History== In the 1850s, Hotchkiss was employed as a [[gunsmith]] in [[Hartford, Connecticut|Hartford]], working on [[Colt's Manufacturing Company|Colt]] revolvers and [[Winchester rifle]]s. He went to France in 1867 and organized '''Hotchkiss & Co.''' in 1875, setting up offices in [[Paris]] and manufacturing facilities in [[Saint-Denis, Seine-Saint-Denis|Saint-Denis]]. This company enjoyed success and the confidence of [[French people|French]] authorities, receiving large governmental orders and was allowed to export arms to other countries. In 1884, Hotchkiss and [[William Armstrong, 1st Baron Armstrong|William Armstrong & Co.]] of [[England]] agreed to manufacture Hotchkiss guns at the [[Elswick Ordnance Company|Elswick]] works. Hotchkiss died in 1885 and in 1887, the affairs of both companies were placed under the French corporation and renamed respectively, the [[Hotchkiss et Cie|Société Anonyme des Anciens Etablissements Hotchkiss et Cie]] of France and the '''Hotchkiss Ordnance Company, Ltd.''' in England.<ref>{{cite web | last =Chinn | first = George M. | title = The Machine Gun, History, Evolution, and Development of Manual, Automatic, and Airborne Repeating Weapons | url= http://www.ibiblio.org/hyperwar/USN/ref/MG/I/MG-2.html#8 | accessdate = 2013-05-27}}</ref> ==References== {{Reflist}} {{Commons category|Hotchkiss}}
